# Generated by Cargo
# will have compiled files and executables
debug
target

# These are backup files generated by rustfmt
**/*.rs.bk

# MSVC Windows builds of rustc generate these, which store debugging information
*.pdb

# Generated by cargo mutants
# Contains mutation testing data
**/mutants.out*/

# RustRover
#  JetBrains specific template is maintained in a separate JetBrains.gitignore that can
#  be found at https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/Global/JetBrains.gitignore
#  and can be added to the global gitignore or merged into this file.  For a more nuclear
#  option (not recommended) you can uncomment the following to ignore the entire idea folder.
#.idea/


# Added by cargo

/target

# Integration-test mutex lock. PID-stamped; cleaned up by Drop /
# OS handle close. See itest-harness::lock + xtask/src/itest.rs.
# Unanchored — running xtask itest from a non-root cwd creates the
# lock relative to that cwd; we want all of them ignored.
.itest.lock

# Pending partial baseline from an interrupted itest run.
# Promote with `cargo xtask itest --promote-pending` or discard with
# `--discard-pending`. Same anywhere-cwd reasoning as above.
.itest-baseline.toml.pending

# Per-run history directories (tier 2 NDJSON + tier 3 log copies).
# One subdir per itest invocation. Pruned manually or by
# `cargo xtask itest --prune-runs`. Explicit `**/` makes the
# at-any-depth match unambiguous (a trailing-slash-only pattern
# anchored unexpectedly here on git 2.50).
.itest-runs

# Locally-rendered diagram SVGs (`cargo xtask diagram <target>` writes these
# next to the committed mermaid .md). Graphviz layout is version-dependent, so
# they're a local-dev convenience, not a reviewable artifact. The .md is the
# committed source of truth.
docs/generated/*.svg
docs/*.svg
docs/*.png

# Built executables injected into the fs image at build time (kernel/build.rs
# copies them here for SpawnImage). Source files in fs-image/ are committed; the
# generated ELFs under fs-image/bin/ are not.
fs-image/bin/
